        <p class="service-description">
          Also known as plantar warts, verruca are viral in origin (Human Papilloma Virus HPV) and typically occur under the feet and
          around the toes. They can spread as well as being unsightly and painful. Verrucae can be difficult to get rid of
          with self-treatment products alone. Our service can offer a
          <b>range of treatment options including chemical and cryotherapy (freezing)
          </b>. When appropriately targeted by a podiatrist, these treatments can be very effective.
        </p>

