        <h4 class="service-title wow fadeInRight">Bunions (Hallux Valgus)</h4>

        <p class="service-description">
          Bunions can be unsightly as well as cause pain and restrict choice of footwear. This condition involves enlargement of the
          big toe joint and sometimes the little toe joint too (known as a tailors bunion). Progression may vary from a small
          localized bump to angling of the big toe sideways, pushing the second toe upwards. Bunions can therefore effect
          the whole front of the foot. Pain can either occur from changes within the joint or from rubbing and squeezing
          over the bump. The condition is mainly hereditary but can be influenced by factors such as weight, pregnancy and
          footwear. Feet foremost has a range of practical solutions for management of discomfort and can advise and help
          in limiting the progression of the deformity with
          <b>footwear</b> and
          <b>orthotic management</b>. Where appropriate we can also advise and direct you surgical options.
        </p>


